cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the threat of data poisoning in machine learning algorithms. It also involves the use of deep learning architectures, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the application of the proposed algorithm in spam filtering and malware detection, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the use of handwritten digit recognition suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper involves the optimization of gradients, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
